GoFTPd Changelog
================

1.1.0b
------

- Expanded built-in SITE command coverage and user management:
  - added `SITE CHANGE`
  - added `SITE CHNUMLOGINS`, `CHMAXSIM`, `CHWKLYALLOTMENT`,
    `CHUPLOADSLOTS`, `CHDOWNLOADSLOTS`, `GROUPSLOTS`, `GROUPSIMULT`,
    `BAN`, `UNBAN`, `BLOWFISH`, `TAGLINE`, and `NUKES`
  - added `SITE ALLUP`, `ALLDN`, `WKUP`, `WKDN`, `DAYUP`, `DAYDN`,
    `MONTHUP`, and `MONTHDN`
  - tightened built-in siteop/gadmin command boundaries so group admins are
    limited to adding users for their own managed groups
- Added persistent nuke history in `userdata/nukes.db` and wired both manual
  and automatic nukes through the same history path, including stored reason,
  multiplier, affected users, bytes, credits, and unnuke tracking.
- Added persistent weekly allotment state in `userdata/weekly_allotment.db`
  so weekly credit replacement survives restarts and only reapplies once per
  week.
- Added banlist-backed login bans in `etc/banlist.txt`.
- Clarified `SITE CHANGE` usage around canonical field names and removed the
  extra compatibility aliases from that command.
- Expanded the shipped userfile model and defaults:
  - fuller compatibility fields such as `LOGINS`, `LOGINSLOTS`, `MAXSIM`,
    `UPLOADSLOTS`, `DOWNLOADSLOTS`, `WKLYALLOTMENT`, `GROUPSLOTS`, and
    `PRIMARY_GROUP`
  - corrected runtime enforcement for login slots, max simultaneous
    transfers, upload/download slots, weekly allotment, and grouped admin
    allowances
  - allowed managed-group leech assignment only through the narrow leech-slot
    path while keeping full ratio changes siteop-only
- Refreshed README and wiki content for the newer slave-mode, remerge, and
  transfer behavior.

1.0.9b
------

- Preserved more VFS directory metadata across restarts and reused cached VFS
  state on the first slave reconnect after master startup instead of forcing a
  pointless initial full remerge.
- Fixed race-complete and race-stats announce edge cases caused by stale
  live-transfer state and over-aggressive complete dedupe.
- Fixed race-complete timing around the last uploaded file so `COMPLETE` and
  follow-up stats lines no longer disappear on successful finishes.
- Reduced race polling pressure on slaves by keeping fresh transfer-state
  reads limited to the completion-critical paths.

1.0.8b
------

- Reduced routine console noise:
  - quieter master/slave non-debug logging
  - hidden routine slave command spam unless debug logging is enabled
  - trimmed successful transfer checksum chatter while keeping mismatch
    warnings
- Tightened slave-mode config handling so slave roots are explicit and
  role-specific config expectations are clearer.
- Refined sitebot output and themes:
  - bandwidth plugin uses the configured site name instead of a hardcoded
    daemon name
  - failed-login staff notices include ready-to-copy ban hints for rejected
    IPs
  - race stats labels/colors were cleaned up, including `ALLUP` naming and
    more consistent rank, speed, and header styling

1.0.7b
------

- Reworked the active/passive transfer path for better secure FXP and
  passthrough stability, including cleaner SSCN/CPSV state handling,
  corrected active TLS role behavior, deferred slave connect timing, and
  tighter transfer-state handoff between master and slave.
- Improved live race transfer behavior, including better secure active upload
  handling, cleaner duplicate-file responses, and more consistent complete
  banner timing under load.
- Added handling for zip-integrity slave responses and improved rescan /
  remerge reporting during large recovery runs.

1.0.6b
------

- Added short post-kick tempbans to `slowkick` so slow users cannot
  reconnect immediately and reclaim the same race slot.
- Extended `slowkick` to watch slow downloads too, with separate
  upload/download thresholds and staff-channel announce events.
- Added the first `spacekeeper` daemon plugin as a master-side free-space
  cleaner that deletes the oldest eligible releases from configured virtual
  paths when a slave drops below its configured free-space threshold.
- Extended `spacekeeper` with archive relocation rules, optional
  dated-folder protection so date buckets are not selected as
  cleanup/archive targets, and background archive jobs including real
  cross-slave archive moves when the archive path routes to another slave.
- Tightened `spacekeeper` archive rules so archive moves are also gated by
  low free space on the watched source slave instead of running every cycle.
- Hardened ACL reloads so malformed `permissions.yml` YAML fails cleanly
  instead of silently degrading into a broken live permissions view.
- Added a `pretime` daemon plugin that can look up release pre times from
  SQLite, MySQL, PostgreSQL, or HTTP/JSON sources and append `NEWPRETIME` /
  `OLDPRETIME` announces for new release dirs.
- Added a sitebot-side `quota` plugin for trial/quota tracking, staff
  `!quotactl` management, and disabled-user enforcement tied to flag `6`.
- Fixed `SITE RESCAN` for music sorting so refreshed audio metadata also
  rebuilds the genre/artist/year/group sort-tree links.
- Made music sort buckets section-aware by default so MP3 and FLAC no longer
  land in the same genre/year/artist/group trees unless explicitly configured.

1.0.5b
------

- Reworked the in-memory VFS so directory listings use direct child indexes
  instead of broad global scans.
- Added cached race-state reads and RaceDB-backed release search to reduce
  hot-path overhead during browsing and racing.
- Switched the shipped ACL examples to root-based paths (`/PRE`, `/MP3`, etc.)
  and cleaned up the structured permissions examples.
- Moved PRE affil visibility management fully into the PRE plugin so
  `affils.yml` stays the source of truth and generated ACL rules stay in sync.
- Added slave-control hardening:
  - IP allowlist support
  - auth-failure temp bans
  - persistent denylist file
  - `SITE SLAVEBANS`, `SITE SLAVEBAN`, and `SITE SLAVEUNBAN`
- Added the built-in `slowkick` plugin to warn and kick slow uploaders and
  downloaders, with staff-channel announcements.
- Added DH1080 auto-exchange for encrypted PM/NOTICE traffic in the sitebot.
- Fixed a race where very fast slave acknowledgements could arrive before the
  master had registered its waiter, causing random upload timeout failures.
- Fixed zip zipscript handling for `0DAY` and `EBOOKS`:
  - blocks manual `file_id.diz` uploads
  - extracts `file_id.diz` from uploaded archives
  - parses more real-world DIZ count formats
  - uses the recovered count for progress, halfway, and complete banners
- Fixed missing or inconsistent `NEW` announces by synthesizing `NEW` from the
  first real upload when a clean `MKDIR` announce was missed.
- Fixed dated-dir announce handling for layouts such as
  `/0DAY/2026-04-26/release/`.
- Fixed section resolution for nested roots like `FOREIGN`, `PRE`, and
  `ARCHIVE` so announces route to the correct child section.
- Fixed `SITE RESCAN` for audio releases so cached music metadata such as genre
  and year is refreshed again for complete banners.
- Fixed parent incomplete markers for zip releases.
- Fixed root and section banner leakage so race banners only appear where they
  make sense, and made the normal CWD banner configurable.
- Fixed topic command behavior and PM encryption flow in the sitebot.

1.0.4b
------

- Added the built-in zipscript module with tighter ZIP and SFV handling.
- Added `SITE BW` plus sitebot `!bw`.
- Added `SITE REMERGE`.
- Added request plugin improvements and public request handling.
- Added configurable log mirroring and log retention controls.
- Added music genre to COMPLETE banners.
- Added section directory creation on slaves and better request visibility on
  CWD.
- Fixed nested section routing and release detection for sitebot announces.
- Fixed incomplete markers for dated release dirs and section roots.
- Fixed private-path event suppression and improved normal-user listing
  behavior.

1.0.3b
------

- Introduced the unified `setup.sh` flow and split plugin configs into
  `config.yml.dist` templates.
- Added setup-driven TLS certificate generation and more complete interactive
  config handling.
- Added self-service IP management and autonuke support.
- Added version propagation into startup banners and media banners.
- Added built-in site user and group management improvements.
- Improved logging defaults, disabled debug in shipped examples, and tightened
  rehash output.
- Improved race stat formatting and restored cached SFV state during reconcile.

1.0.2b
------

- Large architecture refresh of daemon and sitebot internals.
- Added async plugin flow, unified config layout, and broader IRC output
  cleanup.
- Added `SITE PRE`, PREBW support, dated sections, `SITE REHASH`, and
  `SITE INVITE`.
- Added MLST/MLSD support and cbftp-related listing fixes.
- Added metadata lookup groundwork and IMDb rewrite work.
- Improved race speed handling and general announce routing.

1.0.1b
------

- Fixed bcrypt password handling.
- Fixed wrong output from several SITE commands.
- Improved race rendering and race database plumbing.
- Expanded site user management behavior.

1.0.0b
------

- Initial beta baseline for the current GoFTPd codebase.
- Core FTP daemon, sitebot, VFS, ACL, and race-tracking foundations in place.
